'Genistein' is a phytoestrogen and belongs to the category of isoflavones.
Genistein was first isolated in 1899 from the dyer's broom, ''Genista
tinctoria''; hence, the chemical name derived from the generic name. The
compound nucleus was established in 1926, when it was found to be identical with
prunetol. It was chemically synthesized in 1928.
